@mehrdada @nicolasnoble do the binary packages that are released embed boringssl by default? If so we do not have to gate them. If there are any packages that use system openssl but not boringssl, we should hold off on them, especially if they are versions that do not support ALPN.

If the issue is mainly exposed with C++ build, we can 'release' C++ in some way after this fix goes in? Not sure if that would mean just bumping the patch version for C++.

IIUC from offline discussions this should be a reasonably straightforward fix in the makefile, if so could it please be prioritized?

